  <text>
    <body>
      <pb n="1"/>
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <date when="1873-07-23">July 23<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi> 3</date>
          </dateline>
          <salute>Dear <persName ref="#stillja">James</persName>:</salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
          I forwarded to you yesterday<lb/> by <placeName>Boston</placeName> steamship line, one<lb/> box of books containing 20 copies of the<lb/> english <unclear reason="faded" unit="word" quantity="2" resp="#jd">cloth 18do</unclear> paneled style and 10do<lb/> of the <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">Morgan Library</unclear> style of bindings,<lb/> making 48 in all. <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">From</unclear> you therefore<lb/> Mr <persName>Somers</persName> can draw and pay as he goes.<lb/> I wrote him that I should send you a<lb/> box and that he would have the opportunity<lb/> of drawing his supply <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">from</unclear><lb/> you. <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">Also</unclear> I urged him to try and get jobs <unclear reason="faded" resp="#jd">in</unclear> to take their books immediately<lb/> as far as he can do so. The freight will<lb/> be 15 cents on the boat then the <unclear reason="faded" unit="word" quantity="2" resp="#jd">porterage from</unclear><lb/> the wharf to your house will be something-<lb/> let me know what it all comes to and<lb/> I will forward you the money or you<lb/> can deduct it from sales.
        </p>
        <p>
	      Mr. <persName ref="#wileyeda">Wiley</persName> has been home for a<lb/> few days after an absence of 3 months<lb/> successful canvass in <placeName><choice><sic>Pittsburg</sic><corr>Pittsburgh</corr></choice></placeName>.<lb/> On Friday he is going to <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> to operate where doubtless he will be<lb/> very successful. I hardly think he will stop in<lb/> the coal yard this winter.
        </p>
        <p>
          <add place="top-left" rend="vertical"><persName ref="#stillan">Angie</persName> &amp; <persName ref="#stilllu"><unclear resp="#jd">Crece</unclear></persName> were down Monday and reported that all were well at home<lb/> <persName ref="#stillwi"> W.S.</persName></add>
        </p>
        <closer>
          <salute>Yours affectionately</salute>
          <signed><persName ref="#stillwi"><choice><abbr>W</abbr><expan>William </expan></choice> Still</persName></signed>
        </closer>
    </body>
